<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3422] Embedded returns wrong value for DatabaseMetaData.autoCommitFailureClosesAllResultSets()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3422</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;DatabaseMetaData.autoCommitFailureClosesAllResultSets() returns false both on the client and on embedded. However, the embedded driver does in fact close all open result sets when an error occurs in auto-commit mode. There is a test case in jdbc4.TestDbMetaData to test this (testAutoCommitFailure), but it only uses ResultSet.isClosed() to check whether or not the result set is closed after the failure. Because of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3404&quot; title=&quot;EmbedResultSet.getString() returns wrong value after auto-commit with CLOSE_CURSORS_AT_COMMIT&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-3404&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-3404&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, isClosed() returns false for the result sets that have been closed because of the failure, so the test doesn&apos;t reveal the bug. If the test is changed to invoke methods on the result set (e.g. next()) instead of calling isClosed(), we&apos;ll see that the result set is in fact closed and get an SQLException with SQL state XCL16.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12388765">DERBY-3422</key>
