                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12569280" author="knutanders" created="Fri, 15 Feb 2008 14:53:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch which updates the test so that it exposes the bug. Instead of calling isClosed(), it calls ResultSet.next() and checks whether an exception with SQL state XCL16 is thrown. With this change, the test fails on embedded and passes on the client.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12569584" author="knutanders" created="Sat, 16 Feb 2008 16:06:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached is a patch that changes the return value for EmbedDatabaseMetadata40.autoCommitFailureClosesAllResultSets() and updates TestDbMetaData.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When this patch is applied, autoCommitFailureClosesAllResultSets() returns different values on embedded and on the client, so if the approach is accepted and the patch is committed, we should also file an issue to track the difference between client and embedded.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12570630" author="knutanders" created="Wed, 20 Feb 2008 09:36:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 629395.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12570633" author="knutanders" created="Wed, 20 Feb 2008 09:52:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3436&quot; title=&quot;Embedded closes all open ResultSets on failure in auto-commit mode, whereas client keeps them open&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-3436&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-3436&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is logged to track the difference between embedded and client.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12572134" author="mamtas" created="Mon, 25 Feb 2008 17:24:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged revision 629395 from trunk into 10.3.2.2 codeline(630941). The reason for merge is that I would like to merge changes for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3304&quot; title=&quot;Explicit commit inside a java procedure makes a dynamic result sets passed out unavailable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-3304&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-3304&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (629926) into trunk but that revision depends on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3404&quot; title=&quot;EmbedResultSet.getString() returns wrong value after auto-commit with CLOSE_CURSORS_AT_COMMIT&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-3404&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-3404&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (629712) which depends on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3422&quot; title=&quot;Embedded returns wrong value for DatabaseMetaData.autoCommitFailureClosesAllResultSets()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-3422&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-3422&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (629395)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
